      "finding": "Skew of off-diagonal whitened cosines significantly predicts per-model alpha (r=-0.757, p=0.011). Signal is strongest for small-K datasets (AG News K=4: p=0.039) and absent for large-K (Banking77 K=77: p=0.889). This is theoretically consistent: equicorrelation assumption is weakest for small K where few competitors prevent CLT convergence.",
